'''空天'''（{{lang-en|'''Empty Sky'''}}）是一座位於[[美国|美国]][[新泽西州|新泽西州]]的官方纪念牆，纪念在[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]（包括[[世界贸易中心|世界贸易中心]]、[[五角大楼|五角大楼]]和[[賓夕法尼亞州|賓夕法尼亞州]][[尚克斯維爾_(賓夕法尼亞州)|尚克斯維爾]]）以及[[1993年世界贸易中心爆炸案|1993年世界贸易中心爆炸案]]中遇难的746名新澤西州受害者<ref name="foundation">[http://www.nj911memorial.org NJ 911 Memorial Foundation website] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nj911memorial.org/ |date=20100918023621 }}, retrieved February 20, 2011.</ref>。纪念牆位于[[泽西市|泽西市]]的自由州立公园（{{lang|en|Liberty State Park}}），舊新澤西中央鐵路總站（{{lang|en|Central Railroad of New Jersey Terminal}}）旁邊，隔[[哈德遜河|哈德遜河]]口與世貿中心原址相望。紀念牆由潔西卡‧傑姆洛茲（{{lang|en|Jessica Jamroz}}）與弗雷德里克·施瓦茲（{{lang|en|Frederic Schwartz}}）設計，並於九一一事件10周年前一天—2011年9月10日揭幕。<ref name="foundation"/><ref name = opening>{{Citation | last = Calefati | first = Jessica | title = Empty Sky 9/11 memorial opens in Jersey City with emotional ceremony | newspaper = The Star-Ledger | date = September 10, 2011 | url = http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2011/09/911_memorial_jersey_city.html | accessdate = 2011-09-10 | quote =  | archive-date = 2018-11-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181116102451/https://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2011/09/911_memorial_jersey_city.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

==設計==
[[File:A_Night_through_the_Empty_Sky_Memorial.jpg|thumb]]]]
[[File:9-11_Night_Walk_-_panoramio.jpg|thumb]]

共有320份來自世界各地的紀念碑設計入選，並由“家屬與倖存者紀念委員會”（{{lang|en|Families and Survivors Memorial Committee}}）以不記名票從中選出。<ref name="nj">[http://www.state.nj.us/nj911memorial NJ 911 Memorial page] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110321221751/http://www.state.nj.us/nj911memorial |date=2011-03-21|accessdate=2011-02-20}}</ref> 空天紀念在1993年世貿爆炸案於世貿中心、以及2001年九一一襲擊中於世貿中心、五角大廈和賓夕法尼亞州尚克斯維爾罹難的746位新澤西州人。<ref name="foundation">[http://www.nj911memorial.org NJ 911 Memorial Foundation website], retrieved February 20, 2011.</ref>新澤西九一一紀念基金會（{{lang|en|The New Jersey 9/11 Memorial Foundation}}）表示豎立空天紀念碑的目的是“回顧罹難者的事蹟。他們未及實現的夢想和希望照亮我們的未來，他們的品性令我們的生活無比充實。這座紀念牆讓他們的故事永垂不朽。”<ref name="foundation"/>

空天主體包含兩面平行的雙子牆，牆中央是一條把一座緩坡小丘削切為兩半的[[花崗岩|花崗岩]]小徑，而小徑指向的就是世界貿易中心遺址“{{lang|en|Ground Zero}}”。<ref name="foundation" /> 這兩面長方形的牆高{{Convert|30|ft|}}，長度為{{Convert|208|ft|10|in}}—這正正是原世界貿易中心大樓的邊長，而牆的長高比例也跟世貿大樓一樣，象徵大樓倒在地上。<ref name="foundation" />746名罹難者的名字蝕刻在牆上的[[不鏽鋼|不鏽鋼]]板，每個英文字母寬{{Convert|4|in|cm}}。兩道牆之間的小徑指向哈德遜河對岸的世貿雙子塔遺址。<ref name="foundation" /><ref name="opening">{{Citation | last = Calefati | first = Jessica | title = Empty Sky 9/11 memorial opens in Jersey City with emotional ceremony | newspaper = The Star-Ledger | date = 2011-09-10 | url = http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2011/09/911_memorial_jersey_city.html | access-date = 2011-09-10 }}</ref>纪念墙的名字取自[[布魯斯·斯普林斯汀|布魯斯·斯普林斯汀]]的同名歌曲《{{lang|en|Empty Sky}}》。<ref name="schwartz">[http://www.schwartzarch.com/press/PDFs/design_today-memorials.pdf Design News, SchwarchArch.com] {{Wayback|url=http://www.schwartzarch.com/press/PDFs/design_today-memorials.pdf |date=20160322043541 }}, retrieved February 20, 2011.</ref>

設計者之一的弗雷德里克·施瓦茲<ref>[http://www.schwartzarch.com/office.html Jessica Jamroz associate bio, SchwartzArch.com website] {{Wayback|url=http://www.schwartzarch.com/office.html |date=20211115230428 }}, retrieved August 9, 2011.</ref>表示他（的設計）“聆聽了罹難者家屬、朋友和工作伙伴的需要和願望”，同時沒有“預設的審美觀”。<ref name="nyt">Dunlap, David, [https://www.nytimes.com/2004/09/09/nyregion/09profile.html?_r=1&ref=fredericschwartz "For Two 9/11 Memorials, A Man Who Listened," ''The New York Times'', September 9, 2004], retrieved February 20, 2011.</ref>施瓦茲和另一位設計者潔西卡‧傑姆洛茲亦設計了位於[[紐約州|紐約州]][[西徹斯特郡|西徹斯特郡]]的另一座九一一事件紀念碑—「上升」（{{lang|en|The Rising}}），他說：“每個設計都是從頭開始…大量的資料搜集、深入探索建築現場和設計本身。”<ref name="nyt"/>

一些观察家注意到，纪念墙“让人联想到位於[[华盛顿|华盛顿]]、由美籍華裔[[建築師|建築師]][[林璎|林璎]]設計的[[越战纪念碑|越战纪念碑]]”<ref name="boxer">Boxer, Sarah, [http://wirednewyork.com/forum/showthread.php?t=5084&page=1 "New Jersey Selects Its 9/11 Memorial," July 1, 2004] {{Wayback|url=http://wirednewyork.com/forum/showthread.php?t=5084&page=1 |date=20111001203230 }}, retrieved February 20, 2011.</ref>，例如刻滿名字的牆觸手可及，刻字深度足夠讓人用手撫摸得到；但兩者也有諸多不同，例如空天如何利用倒下的雙子塔這個象徵，從視覺上把新澤西和紐約市的[[天際線|天際線]]連結起來。

建造工程开始于2009年5月，2011年8月15日完成。2011年9月10日星期六，九一一袭击十周年的前一天揭幕。<ref name="hudson">Kaulesser, Ricardo, Hudson Reporter, [http://www.hudsonreporter.com/view/full_story/9381718/article-%E2%80%98Empty-Sky%E2%80%99-no-longer-up-in-the-air-Next-phase-of-state%E2%80%99s-9-11-memorial-project-going-forward-despite-opposition-- "Empty Sky no longer 'up in the air'"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hudsonreporter.com/view/full_story/9381718/article-%E2%80%98Empty-Sky%E2%80%99-no-longer-up-in-the-air-Next-phase-of-state%E2%80%99s-9-11-memorial-project-going-forward-despite-opposition-- |date=20110320233422 }}, retrieved February 20, 2011.</ref>。新泽西州州长[[克里斯·克里斯蒂|克里斯·克里斯蒂]] ，五位前州长，等许多著名的政治人物参加了揭幕仪式<ref>{{Cite web | title = Thousands gather i Liberty State Park to dedicate Empty Sky Memorial for NJ 9/11 victims | work =  | publisher = CBS | date = September 10, 2011 | url = http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/09/10/thousands-gather-in-liberty-state-park-to-dedicate-empty-sky-memorial-for-nj-911-victims/ | accessdate = 2011-09-10 | quote =  | archive-date = 2019-09-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190930143827/https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/09/10/thousands-gather-in-liberty-state-park-to-dedicate-empty-sky-memorial-for-nj-911-victims/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>总统顾问约翰·布伦南<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hudsonreporter.com/view/full_stories_home/15459176/article--Obama-sends-cabinet-member-to-state-9-11-memorial-ceremony-in-Jersey-City-?instance=up_to_the_minute_lead_story_left_column |title=存档副本 |access-date=2016-12-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906034658/http://www.hudsonreporter.com/view/full_stories_home/15459176/article--Obama-sends-cabinet-member-to-state-9-11-memorial-ceremony-in-Jersey-City-?instance=up_to_the_minute_lead_story_left_column |archive-date=2017-09-06 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>、参议员弗兰克·劳滕贝格、罗伯特·梅嫩德斯以及遇难者家属<ref name = opening/><ref>{{Citation | last = Katz | first = Matt | title = 9/11 memorial in Jersey City frames view of the empty sky above twin towers site | newspaper = Philadelphia Enquirer | date = September 10, 2011 | url = http://articles.philly.com/2011-09-09/news/30135245_1_empty-sky-memorial-at-ground-zero-towers | accessdate = 2011-09-10 | quote =  | archive-date = 2016-03-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160303231802/http://articles.philly.com/2011-09-09/news/30135245_1_empty-sky-memorial-at-ground-zero-towers | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Citation | last = Brody | first = Leslie | title = 'Empty Sky:' Homage to New Jersey's 9/11 dead | newspaper = The Record | date = September 10, 2011 | url = http://www.northjersey.com/news/128864768_HOMAGE_TO_NEW_JERSEY_S_9_11_DEAD.html | accessdate = 2011-09-10 | quote =  | archive-date = 2012-10-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121002060748/http://www.northjersey.com/news/128864768_HOMAGE_TO_NEW_JERSEY_S_9_11_DEAD.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

